Circuit breaker and retry are complementary resilience patterns: retry handles transient failures by reattempting requests, while circuit breaker prevents system overload by stopping calls when failures exceed a threshold. 
In production systems, retry is typically executed inside the circuit breaker to avoid inflating failure counts and triggering premature circuit opening.

